act.article:
2 Definitions. 

1 In these rules, unless the context 
otherwise requires, 

 a Act means the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000); 
 b Chairperson means the Chairperson of the Cyber Appellate Tribunal 
  appointed under section 49 of the Act; 
 c Committee means a Committee constituted under subrule (2) of rule 3; 

 d Member means the Member of a Cyber Appellate Tribunal appointed under 
  section 49 of the Act; 
 e Tribunal means the Cyber Appellate Tribunal established under 
  sub-section (1) of section 48 of the Act. 

2 All other words and expressions used but not defined in these rules shall 
have the meaning respectively assigned to them in the Act.
